guyana a major sugar producer will 
import sugar from mexico for domestic consumption and use its 
stockpile to meet european commitments the government said 
the staterun guyana sugar corp said thursday that extremely low 
production this year forced it to purchase 4000 tons of sugar from 
mexico and scale down its annual sugar harvest target from 210000 
to 170000 tons 
guyana the englishspeaking caribbeans largest sugar producer 
earns most of its foreign exchange from sugar rice and bauxite it 
has never had to import sugar before 
last week the company said it was unable to meet its us quota 
of 10000 tons and asked jamaica and belize to take up the slack 
under a 1984 agreement 
the company said a fourweek strike in january a drought lasting 
until may and periodic work stoppages are to blame for the low 
production 
