<TEXT>
al raby a former aide to the rev martin luther 
king and manager of harold washingtons 1983 mayoral campaign has 
died of an apparent heart attack he was 55 
raby like washington a year ago died on the eve of thanksgiving 
he was pronounced dead wednesday evening at northwestern memorial 
hospital said hospital spokesman james henri 
raby grew up in poverty on the south side dropped out of school 
and did not earn his elementary school diploma until he was 24 but 
he then continued his education and became an english teacher 
raby participated in the civil rights movement during the early 
1960s and was a leader in kings openhousing marches in chicago and 
other cities in the urban north 
al raby was probably the single biggest reason that dr martin 
luther king came to chicago the rev jesse jackson said al 
helped to lead the open housing movement in the city 
in 1977 raby moved to washington and became an intergovernmental 
liaison in the carter administration with action which oversaw the 
peace corps 
in 1983 raby managed washingtons historic campaign in which he 
won a threeway democratic primary and went on to defeat republican 
bernard epton to become the citys first black mayor raby 
subsequently lost the democratic primary for washingtons 1st 
district congressional seat and washington appointed him director of 
the citys commission on human relations 
im so deeply saddened said the rev willie barrow director 
of operation push a civil rights group he was really my mentor 
in terms of civil rights 
one year ago the city was in deep grief because of the loss of 
our mayor and now one year later a great leader and ambassador of 
race relations has left us ms barrow said 
raby recently founded a public interest firm known as the 
haymarket group 
he also was a member of a panel of black and jewish leaders 
formed in the wake of strained relations between the groups earlier 
this year because of antisemitic remarks made by an aide to mayor 
eugene sawyer 
raby is survived by two daughters kathy and allison and two 
grandchildren 
</TEXT>
