a new family code made public thursday 
will ban polygamy limit prices men pay for brides and eliminate 
alimony because it is unknown by african traditions 
the code to take effect in january 1991 seeks to remove written 
colonial law from family life and return to ancient customs 
the laws published thursday by the official zaire news agency 
azap ban treatments and rites incompatible with human dignity and 
with the respect due to individual freedom under tribal law a 
widow is often married against her will to a member of the dead 
husbands family 
violations are sanctioned by ancient tribal penalties such as 
payment of damages in the form of goats chickens or the ancestral 
wine the code said 
the maximum price men pay for their wives is fixed for each 
region by presidential order it said 
