units of the usual concentrate called factor 8 after declaring it 
was improperly screened for contamination 
as a result many patients needing large amounts of the clotting 
substance must be given cryoprecipitate a relatively crude 
preparation made from fresh plasma that carries a higher risk of 
contamination than the impounded concentrate doctors said 
