execution so clemency petitions could be considered 
so far this year 115 people including three whites have been 
executed while botha has reprieved 49 death row prisoners the 
prison service said more than 200 people still await execution 
the rev stanley mogoba president of south africas methodist 
church said the clemency was one of the best christmas presents i 
can think of 
mr botha has illustrated in this statesmanlike act of 
reprieve that he too understands the christian message of peace and 
good will mogoba said 
i call on him to extend this understanding to others in 
different ways such as releasing political prisoners like mandela 
and dismantling the heretical structures that prop up 
apartheid he added 
the government showed further flexibility in mandelas case 
thursday when justice minister kobie coetsee said the 70yearold 
black leader wont be put back in prison after he recovers from 
tuberculosis 
mandela will be moved to a suitable comfortable and secure 
location from a private clinic where he is hospitalized coetsee 
said in a statement 
mandela head of the outlawed african national congress was 
sentenced to life in prison for plotting sabotage against the white 
minority government he has refused to renounce violence in exchange 
for his freedom 
prakash diar lawyer for the sharpeville six was bitter that 
botha gave his clients long prison terms 1825 years instead of 
freeing them 
two of his clients believe that they would be better off if 
they hanged rather than spending such long times in prison diar 
said 
cape towns argus newspaper questioned whether premeditated 
coldblooded murder by policemen should be equated with a crime 
